agent of all time.

550
00:20:23,379 --> 00:20:24,945
Really?

551
00:20:25,014 --> 00:20:26,114
And to do that,

552
00:20:26,181 --> 00:20:29,316
I need to protect my clients.

553
00:20:29,384 --> 00:20:31,118
Come on.

554
00:20:32,753 --> 00:20:34,254
And, uh...

555
00:20:34,322 --> 00:20:37,057
If you want to protect
Ty, tell us what you know.

556
00:20:42,096 --> 00:20:44,297
(chuckles) Let's make a deal.

557
00:20:44,365 --> 00:20:47,233
I'll tell you everything.
You look into something.

558
00:20:47,300 --> 00:20:48,300
Here's a deal.

559
00:20:48,301 --> 00:20:49,601
Tell us everything, and I don't

560
00:20:49,669 --> 00:20:51,003
cuff you in front of your
co-workers and take you in.

561
00:20:51,071 --> 00:20:52,271
I know how this goes.

562
00:20:52,339 --> 00:20:54,540
Ali's a young actress
looking for a break.

563
00:20:54,607 --> 00:20:57,143
An agent promises to
help her out, in exchange,

564
00:20:57,210 --> 00:20:59,530
she's treated them like a party
favor to your star clients.

565
00:20:59,546 --> 00:21:01,280
Okay, okay.

566
00:21:01,348 --> 00:21:03,781
I did call Ali.

567
00:21:03,849 --> 00:21:05,883
I hired her to have sex with Ty.

568
00:21:05,951 --> 00:21:07,452
Wow, seems I wasn't the only one

569
00:21:07,520 --> 00:21:10,055
who wanted the young
virgin to loosen up.

570
00:21:10,122 --> 00:21:11,956
No, I loved the virgin angle.

571
00:21:12,024 --> 00:21:14,459
It's a clean hook, got
him a lot of attention.

572
00:21:15,594 --> 00:21:18,696
But Ty was a mess.

573
00:21:18,764 --> 00:21:20,064
I needed him

574
00:21:20,131 --> 00:21:22,399
to get over his ex.

575
00:21:22,467 --> 00:21:23,534
Why?

576
00:21:25,770 --> 00:21:27,071
Geez.

577
00:21:27,138 --> 00:21:29,906
Popular boy, this Ty... isn't he?

578
00:21:29,974 --> 00:21:32,809
So what, did this anger
his ex or something?

579
00:21:32,877 --> 00:21:36,180
No, it's from his ex,

580
00:21:36,247 --> 00:21:38,214
Debra Macall. She left this behind

581
00:21:38,282 --> 00:21:39,848
one of the many times she came here

582
00:21:39,916 --> 00:21:41,284
trying to find him.

583
00:21:41,351 --> 00:21:43,052
She used to call all the time
trying to get a hold of him.

584
00:21:43,120 --> 00:21:44,387
So, he dated a crazy fan?

585
00:21:44,455 --> 00:21:46,489
He didn't know it at the beginning.

586
00:21:46,557 --> 00:21:49,225
So when I figured it out, he
had already fallen for her.

587
00:21:49,293 --> 00:21:51,694
Oh, suppose I can understand why.

588
00:21:51,761 --> 00:21:52,928
(chuckles)

589
00:21:52,996 --> 00:21:54,829
JOE: See, after a while,
Debra got possessive,

590
00:21:54,897 --> 00:21:55,897
controlling...

591
00:21:55,931 --> 00:21:57,499
she thought she was managing him.

592
00:21:57,567 --> 00:21:59,701
So I told Ty he needed
to break up with her.

593
00:21:59,768 --> 00:22:01,236
He refused.

594
00:22:01,304 --> 00:22:03,972
I made Ty file a restraining order

595
00:22:04,039 --> 00:22:05,574
after she broke a girl's nose

596
00:22:05,641 --> 00:22:06,874
just for buying him a mojito.

597
00:22:06,942 --> 00:22:08,543
Quite a hair trigger on this Debra,

598
00:22:08,611 --> 00:22:10,579
- by the sounds of it.
- Hmm.

599
00:22:10,646 --> 00:22:12,913
If Debra found out

600
00:22:12,981 --> 00:22:15,182
that Ty was with that poor girl...

601
00:22:22,056 --> 00:22:24,625
Hmm. Finally, some rain.

602
00:22:24,692 --> 00:22:26,827
Maybe someone up there
is looking out for us.

603
00:22:26,894 --> 00:22:28,128
I can assure you,

604
00:22:28,195 --> 00:22:30,730
He's in no way
meteorologically inclined.

605
00:22:30,797 --> 00:22:32,037
Apart from the whole Noah thing,

606
00:22:32,065 --> 00:22:34,267
and that was a one-off.

607
00:22:38,705 --> 00:22:39,772
Anyhow, her roommate confirmed

608
00:22:39,840 --> 00:22:41,541
that she took the 4:00 p.m. class, so...

609
00:22:41,609 --> 00:22:43,909
Ty's ex should be out any second now.

610
00:22:43,977 --> 00:22:45,944
I told you you had the wrong man.

611
00:22:46,012 --> 00:22:47,746
Wrong gender as well, apparently.

612
00:22:47,813 --> 00:22:49,014
Finally, we're getting warmer.

613
00:22:49,081 --> 00:22:52,017
Why are you so hell-bent on
proving Ty's not the killer?

614
00:22:52,084 --> 00:22:53,084
Like I've been saying,

615
00:22:53,085 --> 00:22:54,886
I want to punish the real killer.

616
00:22:54,954 --> 00:22:56,255
But why?

617
00:22:56,322 --> 00:22:57,756
Is it 'cause you pushed him
towards Ali at the party?

618
00:22:57,823 --> 00:23:00,559
Well, I don't see what that
has to do with anything.

619
00:23:00,627 --> 00:23:01,993
And I think you're
starting to agree with me.

620
00:23:02,061 --> 00:23:03,894
Otherwise, you wouldn't
be here, would you?

621
00:23:03,962 --> 00:23:05,163
- Bye!
- Bye!

622
00:23:05,230 --> 00:23:07,198
CHLOE: There she is.

623
00:23:07,266 --> 00:23:10,301
(women conversing
indistinctly in distance)

624
00:23:10,369 --> 00:23:11,669
That was great. I'll call you at lunch.

625
00:23:11,736 --> 00:23:13,937
- I'm over here.
- CHLOE: Debra Macall?

626
00:23:14,005 --> 00:23:15,339
I'm Detective Decker, LAPD.

627
00:23:15,407 --> 00:23:17,575
We need to ask you a few
questions about Ty Huntley.

628
00:23:17,643 --> 00:23:19,076
I've got nothing to say.

629
00:23:19,144 --> 00:23:20,704
It's either here or down at the station.

630
00:23:20,744 --> 00:23:22,412
- Leave me alone!
- CHLOE: Debra...

631
00:23:26,850 --> 00:23:29,085
(car alarm blaring, horn honking)

632
00:23:30,321 --> 00:23:32,255
See?

633
00:23:32,323 --> 00:23:33,890
Warmer.

634
00:23:42,120 --> 00:23:43,860
Found this on the undercarriage.

635
00:23:43,915 --> 00:23:45,281
Remote detonator.

636
00:23:45,349 --> 00:23:47,984
Whoever set off this bomb was nearby.

637
00:23:48,051 --> 00:23:49,652
Scour the security cameras in the area.

638
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:53,623
Get facial I.D.'s on anyone
in a hundred-block radius.

639
00:23:53,690 --> 00:23:55,324
LUCIFER: You couldn't live with
yourself for committing murder,

640
00:23:55,392 --> 00:23:57,192
so you set your car
to explode, didn't you?

641
00:23:57,260 --> 00:23:59,261
Eh? Wanted to go out
in a blaze of glory.

642
00:23:59,329 --> 00:24:00,162
Of course not!

643
00:24:00,230 --> 00:24:02,665
Murder? What are you talking about?

644
00:24:02,733 --> 00:24:03,932
LUCIFER: Oh, come on...

645
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:05,280
The bomb was triggered remotely.

646
00:24:05,334 --> 00:24:07,702
Whoever set it off did it
before you got to the car.

647
00:24:07,770 --> 00:24:09,004
There's a clear line of sight.

648
00:24:09,071 --> 00:24:10,672
I don't think the plan was to kill you.

649
00:24:10,740 --> 00:24:12,240
I think they wanted to scare you.

650
00:24:12,307 --> 00:24:15,043
So... you know of any reason why
someone would want to do that?

651
00:24:15,110 --> 00:24:17,045
No.

652
00:24:17,112 --> 00:24:18,647
Yes, why did you run, Debra?

653
00:24:18,714 --> 00:24:20,214
Awfully guilty-looking.

654
00:24:21,282 --> 00:24:22,642
I thought you were going to bust me

655
00:24:22,684 --> 00:24:24,084
for violating my restraining order.

656
00:24:25,020 --> 00:24:26,820
I went to Ty's party last night.

657
00:24:27,756 --> 00:24:28,956
I-I just... I just looked.

658
00:24:29,024 --> 00:24:30,390
From outside, through the window.

659
00:24:30,458 --> 00:24:31,458
I couldn't help it, I miss him.

660
00:24:31,526 --> 00:24:33,928
Yes, breaking up's so hard, isn't it?

661
00:24:33,995 --> 00:24:35,729
You're like two pathetic peas in a pod.

662
00:24:35,797 --> 00:24:37,531
Okay, we are made for each other.

663
00:24:37,598 --> 00:24:39,032
As good as he is at football,

664
00:24:39,099 --> 00:24:41,200
that's how good I am
at being his girlfriend.

665
00:24:41,268 --> 00:24:42,702
You mean ex-girlfriend.

666
00:24:42,770 --> 00:24:44,737
We never stay broken
up. It's just a phase.

667
00:24:44,805 --> 00:24:47,473
And no one looks out for
him the way that I do.

668
00:24:47,541 --> 00:24:50,610
And then I saw him
kissing that girl and I...

669
00:24:50,678 --> 00:24:51,711
Squeezed the life out of her?

670
00:24:51,779 --> 00:24:53,212
DEBRA: No!

671
00:24:54,214 --> 00:24:55,146
Where were you between

672
00:24:55,214 --> 00:24:56,494
1:00 and 3:00 a.m. this morning?

673
00:24:58,051 --> 00:25:01,186
The only place that always
makes me feel better.

674
00:25:01,253 --> 00:25:03,254
(sobbing)

675
00:25:05,524 --> 00:25:06,825
DAN: How long does this go on?

676
00:25:06,893 --> 00:25:08,193
CHLOE: Three hours.

677
00:25:08,260 --> 00:25:10,128
(wry laugh)

678
00:25:10,196 --> 00:25:11,756
That's the saddest thing I've ever seen.

679
00:25:11,797 --> 00:25:14,198
CHLOE: Yep. All-night froyo shop

680
00:25:14,265 --> 00:25:16,567
puts Debra there well past
the time of the victim's death.

681
00:25:16,635 --> 00:25:18,135
Her alibi checks out.

682
00:25:19,537 --> 00:25:21,472
So Debra didn't strangle Ali.

683
00:25:21,539 --> 00:25:23,273
Well, whoever planted the bomb

684
00:25:23,341 --> 00:25:25,610
went to great lengths to
make us think Debra did it.

685
00:25:25,677 --> 00:25:27,144
Why?

686
00:25:27,212 --> 00:25:28,212
I don't know.

687
00:25:31,716 --> 00:25:35,719
We might actually know
who rigged the car.

688
00:25:38,222 --> 00:25:39,222
Ronnie Hillman.

689
00:25:40,390 --> 00:25:42,492
CHLOE: The big Hollywood fixer?

690
00:25:42,559 --> 00:25:43,559
Yeah.

691
00:25:43,628 --> 00:25:44,661
A security cam caught her

692
00:25:44,729 --> 00:25:46,369
walking nearby, right
after the explosion.

693
00:25:46,429 --> 00:25:47,549
This can't be a coincidence.

694
00:25:47,597 --> 00:25:48,957
Someone must've hired her for this.

695
00:25:48,965 --> 00:25:51,266
I've been trying to build
a case on her for years,

696
00:25:51,334 --> 00:25:52,774
and every time we've approached her,

697
00:25:52,802 --> 00:25:54,670
she's lawyered up immediately.

698
00:25:54,738 --> 00:25:55,938
Ronnie is a pro.

699
00:25:56,006 --> 00:25:57,205
So how do we approach her?

700
00:25:57,273 --> 00:25:58,507
She's picky about talking to strangers.

701
00:25:58,574 --> 00:26:01,143
Definitely no cops.

702
00:26:04,880 --> 00:26:06,914
What about someone

703
00:26:06,982 --> 00:26:09,517
she'd never expect us to work with?

704
00:26:09,584 --> 00:26:11,318
LUCIFER: Do I get a code word?

705
00:26:11,386 --> 00:26:13,387
You know, for when you take her down.

706
00:26:13,455 --> 00:26:15,322
If so, might I suggest

707
00:26:15,390 --> 00:26:16,557
"monkey bottoms"?

708
00:26:16,625 --> 00:26:17,905
'Cause trust me, I can work that

709
00:26:17,960 --> 00:26:18,993
into any sentence quite naturally.

710
00:26:19,061 --> 00:26:20,961
You sure this is a good idea?

711
00:26:21,029 --> 00:26:22,262
Lucifer reached out to her

712
00:26:22,329 --> 00:26:24,364
and she agreed to meet
him, so it's our best shot.

713
00:26:24,431 --> 00:26:27,167
And you won't need a code
word, and you won't be miked,

714
00:26:27,234 --> 00:26:28,702
because she'll be looking for that.

715
00:26:28,770 --> 00:26:29,770
This is a simple handoff.

716
00:26:29,804 --> 00:26:31,738
All we need you to do is vouch for Dan

717
00:26:31,806 --> 00:26:33,073
as someone that needs her services.

718
00:26:33,141 --> 00:26:34,875
Vouch for Detective Douche?

719
00:26:34,942 --> 00:26:37,843
Oh, gosh, this is gonna
be harder than I thought.

720
00:26:37,911 --> 00:26:39,311
Once I engage with her, I will hire her

721
00:26:39,379 --> 00:26:40,379
to fix a problem of mine.

722
00:26:40,380 --> 00:26:41,380
Right.

723
00:26:41,414 --> 00:26:42,715
Well, if it's that stick up your ass,

724
00:26:42,783 --> 00:26:44,750
I'm afraid there's no one
strong enough to pull that out.

725
00:26:44,818 --> 00:26:46,138
She goes there to fix my problem,

726
00:26:46,186 --> 00:26:47,853
our people will be
waiting to arrest her.

727
00:26:47,921 --> 00:26:49,055
- Ah.
- CHLOE: And then we'll have leverage

728
00:26:49,122 --> 00:26:50,790
to find out what she
knows about Ali's murder.

729
00:26:50,857 --> 00:26:52,424
She has information we need,

730
00:26:52,492 --> 00:26:53,772
so let's just stick to the plan.

731
00:26:53,826 --> 00:26:55,626
Assuming, of course,
Ronnie hasn't run off

732
00:26:55,695 --> 00:26:56,961
because our sting suddenly turned into

733
00:26:57,029 --> 00:26:58,362
a Michael Bublé concert.

734
00:26:59,799 --> 00:27:00,999
Lucifer, this isn't a game.

735
00:27:01,067 --> 00:27:03,234
- Oh.
- Now, are you up for this or not?

736
00:27:03,302 --> 00:27:07,205
Am I up for encouraging someone
to commit a nefarious act?

737
00:27:07,272 --> 00:27:08,740
Mm, let me think.

738
00:27:08,808 --> 00:27:10,675
Put me in, Coach.

739
00:27:10,742 --> 00:27:12,676
(sighs)

740
00:27:12,744 --> 00:27:16,180
♪ Drown my woes in a lake
of fire, sing a song... ♪

741
00:27:16,247 --> 00:27:18,015
Ooh, lovely moves.

742
00:27:18,083 --> 00:27:19,483
♪ Drown my woes in a lake of fire ♪

743
00:27:19,550 --> 00:27:21,151
♪ Sing a song gonna take me higher... ♪

744
00:27:21,219 --> 00:27:23,253
Try to look even more like a douche.

745
00:27:25,256 --> 00:27:26,489
Mission accomplished.

746
00:27:26,557 --> 00:27:28,224
♪ Lucifer gonna set me free ♪

747
00:27:28,291 --> 00:27:30,993
♪ Good Lord turned his back on me ♪

748
00:27:31,061 --> 00:27:34,130
♪ Lucifer gonna set me free... ♪

749
00:27:34,198 --> 00:27:35,198
She's here.

750
00:27:35,265 --> 00:27:36,999
Okay, great. Here we go.

751
00:27:37,067 --> 00:27:40,002
(music playing over speakers)

752
00:27:40,070 --> 00:27:43,840
♪ Never got no good
doing what I'm told ♪

753
00:27:43,907 --> 00:27:48,409
♪ It's a mean
world that I've known ♪

754
00:27:48,477 --> 00:27:50,345
♪ Now you'll find me where
the devil don't go... ♪

755
00:27:50,412 --> 00:27:53,615
Ronnie Hillman,
problem-solver extraordinaire.

756
00:27:57,319 --> 00:27:59,121
Oh...

757
00:27:59,188 --> 00:28:00,388
(laughs)

758
00:28:00,456 --> 00:28:01,723
Mm, you checking for a wire

759
00:28:01,790 --> 00:28:02,957
or are you just pleased to see me?

760
00:28:03,024 --> 00:28:04,725
(laughs)

761
00:28:04,793 --> 00:28:06,360
Little bit of both.

762
00:28:06,427 --> 00:28:07,527
Mmm! (chuckles)

763
00:28:07,595 --> 00:28:09,263
Hello, Mr. Morningstar.

764
00:28:09,330 --> 00:28:11,732
Rest assured...

765
00:28:11,800 --> 00:28:13,533
I can help you with your problem.

766
00:28:13,601 --> 00:28:16,237
Well, actually, I don't need your help.

767
00:28:16,304 --> 00:28:17,772
I...

768
00:28:17,839 --> 00:28:19,873
Wait, what do you think my problem is?

769
00:28:19,940 --> 00:28:21,775
Impostor running around
ruining your name.

770
00:28:21,842 --> 00:28:25,178
Your professional reputation
has taken a bit of a dive.

771
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:29,949
As has your sexual one, I'm afraid.

772
00:28:30,017 --> 00:28:32,252
All those unsatisfied ladies...

773
00:28:32,319 --> 00:28:34,187
Word gets around.

774
00:28:35,422 --> 00:28:38,190
That is the reason you
reached out to me, isn't it?

775
00:28:42,495 --> 00:28:43,628
Yes.

776
00:28:43,696 --> 00:28:44,930
Yes, it very much is.

777
00:28:44,998 --> 00:28:47,266
I do have a problem
that could use your help.

778
00:28:47,333 --> 00:28:48,533
I am all yours.

779
00:28:48,601 --> 00:28:50,903
Oh! Well, I like you,
monkey bottoms. (chuckles)

780
00:28:50,970 --> 00:28:52,937
Here's what I need you to do...

781
00:28:53,005 --> 00:28:54,205
♪ ... doing what I'm told... ♪

782
00:28:54,273 --> 00:28:56,407
(whispering): Lucifer,
what are you doing?

783
00:28:56,474 --> 00:28:57,675
(music playing over speakers)

784
00:28:57,742 --> 00:28:59,177
Hey, Dan, what's going on?

785
00:29:00,846 --> 00:29:02,413
DAN: I don't know.

786
00:29:02,480 --> 00:29:04,215
They're still talking.

787
00:29:06,751 --> 00:29:09,220
