788
00:29:11,622 --> 00:29:13,223
LUCIFER: Lovely.

789
00:29:14,525 --> 00:29:16,226
What the hell did you do?

790
00:29:16,294 --> 00:29:19,362
I hired the fixer to fix
a problem, like you wanted.

791
00:29:19,430 --> 00:29:20,931
You let her go. What
happened to the plan?

792
00:29:20,998 --> 00:29:23,066
- I made a better one.
- How?

793
00:29:23,134 --> 00:29:24,334
Just sit tight

794
00:29:24,401 --> 00:29:25,836
and we'll all get what we want.

795
00:29:35,554 --> 00:29:37,454
- Finally!
- (whimpers)

796
00:29:37,522 --> 00:29:40,090
The would-be Prince of Darkness.

797
00:29:40,158 --> 00:29:42,092
Payment due upon delivery.

798
00:29:42,160 --> 00:29:43,160
(wry laugh)

799
00:29:43,161 --> 00:29:45,729
I'd like to examine the goods first.

800
00:29:45,797 --> 00:29:46,996
RONNIE: Your dime.

801
00:29:51,101 --> 00:29:52,902
Right.

802
00:29:52,969 --> 00:29:55,438
Let's see the face of my impostor.

803
00:29:58,809 --> 00:30:00,310
(Maze laughs)

804
00:30:01,812 --> 00:30:03,845
The resemblance is uncanny.

805
00:30:06,449 --> 00:30:10,085
It most certainly is not.

806
00:30:10,152 --> 00:30:11,220
(giggling)

807
00:30:11,287 --> 00:30:13,154
How could anyone think that you were me?

808
00:30:13,223 --> 00:30:15,890
(false British accent): You
know who you're messing with?

809
00:30:15,958 --> 00:30:18,126
I'm Lucifer freaking Morningstar!

810
00:30:18,194 --> 00:30:19,661
Oh...

811
00:30:19,729 --> 00:30:20,828
Are you now?

812
00:30:20,895 --> 00:30:23,764
Well... you've certainly
been a busy bee,

813
00:30:23,832 --> 00:30:25,966
haven't you, "Lucifer"?

814
00:30:26,034 --> 00:30:27,204
Eh?

815
00:30:27,205 --> 00:30:29,270
Apparently, you've
started a modeling agency,

816
00:30:29,338 --> 00:30:32,139
pitched a Web series.

817
00:30:33,375 --> 00:30:34,542
And I hear you've also been

818
00:30:34,610 --> 00:30:36,644
very active with the women.

819
00:30:36,712 --> 00:30:37,777
Ladies love me.

820
00:30:37,845 --> 00:30:39,279
What can I say?

821
00:30:39,347 --> 00:30:42,014
It's what they've been
saying that's the trouble.

822
00:30:42,082 --> 00:30:44,917
It seems you're a bit
of a two-pump chump.

823
00:30:44,985 --> 00:30:46,253
Also, a crier afterwards.

824
00:30:46,320 --> 00:30:48,187
That happened one time.

825
00:30:48,256 --> 00:30:51,057
Right. Well, we can't
have you running around

826
00:30:51,125 --> 00:30:52,792
cheapening the Lucifer
brand, now, can we?

827
00:30:52,860 --> 00:30:55,160
What do you say, Maze?

828
00:30:55,228 --> 00:30:56,928
Impalement?

829
00:30:56,996 --> 00:30:58,364
MAZE: Hmm...

830
00:30:58,431 --> 00:31:00,899
Why rush?

831
00:31:00,967 --> 00:31:02,834
- I say the rack.
- Oh.

832
00:31:02,902 --> 00:31:04,436
- Oh!
- Ooh.

833
00:31:04,504 --> 00:31:05,837
That way,

834
00:31:05,905 --> 00:31:07,640
we can really enjoy it.

835
00:31:07,707 --> 00:31:09,575
LUCIFER: Better. Yes, much better.

836
00:31:09,643 --> 00:31:11,809
Every joint of every limb

837
00:31:11,877 --> 00:31:13,611
dislocated before it's torn off.

838
00:31:13,679 --> 00:31:16,681
No, no, no, no, no... look,
look, look, I just... I just...

839
00:31:16,749 --> 00:31:19,183
I just wanted to get
chicks and-and free drinks.

840
00:31:19,251 --> 00:31:21,018
Um, really.

841
00:31:22,020 --> 00:31:23,921
(dropping accent) My name is Justin.

842
00:31:23,989 --> 00:31:24,989
I'm from Sherman Oaks.

843
00:31:24,990 --> 00:31:26,123
(Maze and Lucifer laughing)

844
00:31:26,191 --> 00:31:28,292
Oh, Justin...

845
00:31:28,359 --> 00:31:30,059
the things I'm gonna do to you.

846
00:31:30,127 --> 00:31:31,561
Oh, no, no, no, I-I'm sorry!

847
00:31:31,629 --> 00:31:32,796
I only came here one time

848
00:31:32,863 --> 00:31:34,631
and I just told some girls

849
00:31:34,699 --> 00:31:35,999
that I owned the place, and...

850
00:31:36,066 --> 00:31:37,601
and that opened some doors for me

851
00:31:37,669 --> 00:31:38,868
and so I just started rolling with it.

852
00:31:38,936 --> 00:31:41,672
How dare you abscond my name!

853
00:31:41,739 --> 00:31:43,440
Please, don't hurt me.

854
00:31:43,508 --> 00:31:44,775
Please.

855
00:31:44,842 --> 00:31:46,122
LUCIFER: I'm not gonna hurt you,

856
00:31:46,142 --> 00:31:48,444
Justin, I'm going to destroy you.

857
00:31:48,512 --> 00:31:50,746
Oh, this is so hot.

858
00:31:50,814 --> 00:31:53,683
It's like you're punishing yourself.

859
00:31:59,055 --> 00:32:02,191
Seems I could be just, um,

860
00:32:02,258 --> 00:32:03,858
overreacting a bit.

861
00:32:08,263 --> 00:32:10,031
Go.

862
00:32:10,098 --> 00:32:11,265
Go on!

863
00:32:13,068 --> 00:32:14,803
And never sully my name again.

864
00:32:18,774 --> 00:32:20,441
Let's at least take a finger.

865
00:32:20,508 --> 00:32:21,975
We've done enough, Maze.

866
00:32:29,083 --> 00:32:30,551
Pleasure doing business
with you, Lucifer.

867
00:32:30,618 --> 00:32:31,985
Yes, it was, wasn't it?

868
00:32:32,053 --> 00:32:34,555
Which is why I'm going to have
to apologize for my friends.

869
00:32:34,622 --> 00:32:35,723
What friends?

870
00:32:35,790 --> 00:32:36,989
CHLOE: Ronnie Hillman,

871
00:32:37,057 --> 00:32:39,024
you're under arrest for
kidnapping and assault.

872
00:32:43,630 --> 00:32:45,398
Would you mind calling my lawyer?

873
00:32:45,466 --> 00:32:47,586
(handcuffs tightening) Her
number's in my back pocket.

874
00:32:47,634 --> 00:32:49,101
Yeah, sure thing.

875
00:32:49,169 --> 00:32:50,670
I'll tell her about the kidnapping,

876
00:32:50,738 --> 00:32:52,204
the airtight evidence we have,

877
00:32:52,272 --> 00:32:54,172
the attempted murder on Debra Macall,

878
00:32:54,240 --> 00:32:56,360
and then when we connect
you to Ali Thornton's murder,

879
00:32:56,409 --> 00:32:57,809
maybe you'll get a
nice injection of drugs,

880
00:32:57,877 --> 00:32:59,811
and you can go to sleep forever.

881
00:32:59,879 --> 00:33:04,015
Hang on... I had nothing
to do with Ali's murder.

882
00:33:04,083 --> 00:33:08,253
Debra Macall, Ty Huntley's
ex, she's the murderer.

883
00:33:08,320 --> 00:33:10,021
I cared about Ali.

884
00:33:10,089 --> 00:33:11,422
Mm-hmm, here's what I think.

885
00:33:11,490 --> 00:33:14,324
I think you tried to scare Debra
into confessing to Ali's murder,

886
00:33:14,393 --> 00:33:15,626
but Debra didn't do it.

887
00:33:15,694 --> 00:33:17,395
She's got an ironclad alibi.

888
00:33:20,432 --> 00:33:22,332
This is my fault.

889
00:33:22,401 --> 00:33:24,167
Why?

890
00:33:24,235 --> 00:33:27,871
I promised Ali I would protect her.

891
00:33:27,938 --> 00:33:30,640
All she ever wanted
was to be an actress.

892
00:33:30,708 --> 00:33:32,375
She was gonna leave her mark.

893
00:33:32,443 --> 00:33:33,610
But you know how that goes.

894
00:33:33,677 --> 00:33:36,979
Endless rejection, she ran out of money.

895
00:33:37,047 --> 00:33:39,949
This was her first gig with me.

896
00:33:40,017 --> 00:33:41,951
She didn't even know if she could do it.

897
00:33:42,019 --> 00:33:46,221
But I told her... I told
her it was just like acting.

898
00:33:46,289 --> 00:33:49,525
Besides, who doesn't want
to sleep with Ty Huntley?

899
00:33:49,592 --> 00:33:52,227
I thought Ty's agent hired
Ali to sleep with him.

900
00:33:52,295 --> 00:33:55,464
He hired me for a number
three special: blackmail.

901
00:33:55,532 --> 00:33:58,667
Slip him a roofie, get naked,
whip out a selfie stick,

902
00:33:58,735 --> 00:33:59,935
and voilà.

903
00:34:00,002 --> 00:34:01,702
LUCIFER: Why would he have any desire

904
00:34:01,770 --> 00:34:03,237
to blackmail his own star client,

905
00:34:03,305 --> 00:34:04,839
a client he's all about protecting?

906
00:34:04,907 --> 00:34:07,809
Ty's agent told you
that Debra killed Ali.

907
00:34:07,876 --> 00:34:10,778
He did, yeah.

908
00:34:20,387 --> 00:34:21,855
You think Joe's the killer,

909
00:34:21,923 --> 00:34:24,791
that he took things into his
own hands, quite literally.

910
00:34:24,859 --> 00:34:25,992
We don't have any proof.

911
00:34:26,060 --> 00:34:29,629
Right, well, how do you
propose that we get him?

912
00:34:30,665 --> 00:34:32,599
Joe pointed the finger right at Debra,

913
00:34:32,667 --> 00:34:33,867
painted her as crazy.

914
00:34:33,935 --> 00:34:35,401
It's not that hard a picture
to paint, in her case.

915
00:34:35,469 --> 00:34:38,003
Why was he so certain
she'd make a good suspect?

916
00:34:38,071 --> 00:34:41,106
Maybe he found out
she went to Ty's party.

917
00:34:41,174 --> 00:34:43,709
Maybe he knew she went to Ty's party.

918
00:34:54,461 --> 00:34:58,413
You are looking at
the future of football.

919
00:34:58,481 --> 00:35:00,549
The American Dream.

920
00:35:00,617 --> 00:35:04,953
Honest, resilient, heroic.

921
00:35:05,020 --> 00:35:07,143
The police tried to pin

922
00:35:07,168 --> 00:35:11,293
the death of that poor girl on you.

923
00:35:11,361 --> 00:35:14,128
But we kept it out of the press.

924
00:35:14,195 --> 00:35:17,365
We got you out of jail.

925
00:35:17,432 --> 00:35:19,433
We will always protect you...

926
00:35:19,501 --> 00:35:22,403
and make you a bigger star than ever.

927
00:35:22,471 --> 00:35:25,273
This is Ty Huntley...

928
00:35:25,340 --> 00:35:27,841
rebranded. (laughs)

929
00:35:33,314 --> 00:35:34,314
LUCIFER: Rebranded, eh?

930
00:35:34,382 --> 00:35:36,048
Does it come with a new scent?

931
00:35:36,116 --> 00:35:37,183
Free toy inside?

932
00:35:37,251 --> 00:35:39,118
What do you want?

933
00:35:39,186 --> 00:35:41,521
Ty is free on bail.

934
00:35:41,589 --> 00:35:43,657
We have to talk to Ty
down at the station again,

935
00:35:43,724 --> 00:35:45,458
maybe walk him past a few reporters.

936
00:35:45,526 --> 00:35:47,025
Whoa, hold on, uh, Joe, what is this?

937
00:35:47,093 --> 00:35:48,794
Oh, come on! This is ridiculous.

938
00:35:48,861 --> 00:35:51,029
Ty wouldn't hurt anybody!

939
00:35:51,097 --> 00:35:52,298
What about Debra?

940
00:35:52,365 --> 00:35:53,732
I told you to look into her.

941
00:35:53,800 --> 00:35:54,900
She's the crazy one.

942
00:35:54,967 --> 00:35:56,402
Yes, well, I thought
it was her all along.

943
00:35:56,469 --> 00:35:58,671
I mean, the woman certainly
redefines "intensity."

944
00:35:58,738 --> 00:36:01,540
But Debra was home with a
friend the night of the murder.

945
00:36:01,608 --> 00:36:02,675
What?!

946
00:36:02,742 --> 00:36:03,908
She's lying.

947
00:36:03,975 --> 00:36:05,735
There's no evidence
placing her at the party.

948
00:36:05,744 --> 00:36:06,778
No one saw her.

949
00:36:06,845 --> 00:36:09,246
So are you ready to face the cameras?

950
00:36:09,315 --> 00:36:10,782
His sponsors will love
the free publicity.

951
00:36:10,849 --> 00:36:13,785
Tell me, what's ten percent of nothing?

952
00:36:13,852 --> 00:36:15,520
I saw Debra there.

953
00:36:17,189 --> 00:36:20,390
I went by the party.

954
00:36:20,458 --> 00:36:24,861
But a work call came up,
and I never made it inside.

955
00:36:24,929 --> 00:36:26,496
I didn't say anything before

956
00:36:26,564 --> 00:36:29,333
because I told my wife
I was working late.

957
00:36:29,400 --> 00:36:33,470
When I was driving away, I
saw Debra outside Ty's window.

958
00:36:33,538 --> 00:36:36,139
So you admit you were there that night.

959
00:36:36,207 --> 00:36:38,841
Yeah, and so was Debra.

960
00:36:38,908 --> 00:36:40,188
That's the proof you need, right?

961
00:36:40,210 --> 00:36:41,450
CHLOE: That's the proof we need.

962
00:36:41,511 --> 00:36:43,946
We have a sworn statement
from Ronnie Hillman

963
00:36:44,013 --> 00:36:45,214
saying that you hired the victim

964
00:36:45,281 --> 00:36:47,350
to make a sex tape with
Ty to blackmail him.

965
00:36:47,417 --> 00:36:48,851
I just needed to place you at the scene.

966
00:36:48,918 --> 00:36:50,653
LUCIFER: Yeah, see,
that's why I don't lie.

967
00:36:50,721 --> 00:36:52,722
It's so hard to keep
track of who knows what.

968
00:36:52,789 --> 00:36:54,389
It's not true.

969
00:36:54,457 --> 00:36:56,791
I only want what's best for you, Ty.

970
00:36:56,859 --> 00:36:58,092
You know, I still don't understand.

971
00:36:58,160 --> 00:36:59,794
Why is it my own agent
would want to blackmail me?

972
00:36:59,862 --> 00:37:02,664
Because he thought eventually
you were gonna leave him.

973
00:37:02,732 --> 00:37:04,833
What, because I took one
meeting with another agency?

974
00:37:05,934 --> 00:37:07,001
Joe...

975
00:37:07,069 --> 00:37:08,570
I only did that to make Debra happy.

976
00:37:08,637 --> 00:37:10,037
But even though you'd broken up,

977
00:37:10,105 --> 00:37:11,345
he knew you'd get back together,

978
00:37:11,373 --> 00:37:14,107
so he decided to strike
first, get some leverage.

979
00:37:14,175 --> 00:37:17,411
If he left me, I would be ruined.

980
00:37:17,479 --> 00:37:19,145
I mean, do you understand?

981
00:37:19,213 --> 00:37:20,581
He is my Brady, my Manning.

982
00:37:20,648 --> 00:37:23,283
But Ali wasn't cut out for
this sort of thing, was she?

983
00:37:23,351 --> 00:37:24,885
She didn't want to give you the video.

984
00:37:24,952 --> 00:37:26,520
Stupid bitch.

985
00:37:28,322 --> 00:37:30,990
She said she realized Ty was a good guy.

986
00:37:31,057 --> 00:37:32,291
She didn't want to go through with it.

987
00:37:32,359 --> 00:37:35,695
Her name was Ali Thornton,
and you killed her.

988
00:37:35,763 --> 00:37:36,896
For what?

989
00:37:36,963 --> 00:37:39,031
Greed? Ego?

990
00:37:39,099 --> 00:37:40,299
I didn't want to hurt her.

991
00:37:40,367 --> 00:37:42,902
I just wanted her phone. And...

992
00:37:42,969 --> 00:37:44,837
(Joe sighs)

993
00:37:49,208 --> 00:37:51,410
But I squeezed too hard.

994
00:37:52,978 --> 00:37:54,012
I'm done.

995
00:37:54,079 --> 00:37:56,314
Forget this. I'm out of here.

996
00:38:00,986 --> 00:38:03,320
(gasps)

997
00:38:03,388 --> 00:38:05,222
Did I squeeze too hard?

998
00:38:06,725 --> 00:38:08,926
How did you...?

999
00:38:08,993 --> 00:38:10,193
What did...?

1000
00:38:10,261 --> 00:38:12,195
Lucifer, what are you doing?

1001
00:38:12,263 --> 00:38:14,532
Finally focusing my
anger where it belongs.

1002
00:38:14,599 --> 00:38:15,633
Lucifer...

1003
00:38:18,970 --> 00:38:22,204
(chuckles)

1004
00:38:22,272 --> 00:38:24,808
Yes, of course.

1005
00:38:24,875 --> 00:38:26,375
Your turn, Detective.

1006
00:38:26,444 --> 00:38:29,879
(sirens wailing, radio chatter)

1007
00:38:35,553 --> 00:38:37,986
I still can't believe Joe did this.

1008
00:38:38,054 --> 00:38:41,824
I wasn't ever gonna
leave him, you know that?

1009
00:38:41,891 --> 00:38:43,358
Definitely gonna leave him now.

1010
00:38:43,426 --> 00:38:45,093
But you know what, you, uh...

1011
00:38:45,161 --> 00:38:46,962
you stayed good to your word, Lucifer.

1012
00:38:47,029 --> 00:38:48,129
Thank you.

1013
00:38:48,197 --> 00:38:51,266
Yes, well, now you owe me one.

1014
00:38:53,869 --> 00:38:55,970
DEBRA: Ty!

1015
00:38:56,037 --> 00:38:57,738
Ty! Ty!

1016
00:38:59,541 --> 00:39:00,541
Oh, my baby.

1017
00:39:00,609 --> 00:39:02,142
Oh, my God, I'm so glad to see you.

1018
00:39:02,210 --> 00:39:04,378
- Oh.
- You are?

1019
00:39:04,446 --> 00:39:05,813
Yes, you are crazy, baby.

1020
00:39:05,881 --> 00:39:08,248
- But you're my crazy, you hear me?
- Yeah?

1021
00:39:09,952 --> 00:39:12,385
Warms the cockles, doesn't it?

1022
00:39:13,921 --> 00:39:15,254
So, Detective,

1023
00:39:15,322 --> 00:39:17,023
looks like you've solved another case

1024
00:39:17,091 --> 00:39:18,091
because of me.

1025
00:39:18,092 --> 00:39:19,659
I solved this case despite you.

1026
00:39:19,727 --> 00:39:21,862
What? What about the cell phone I found?

1027
00:39:21,929 --> 00:39:23,129
That was key evidence.

1028
00:39:23,197 --> 00:39:24,498
Evidence you almost destroyed.

1029
00:39:24,565 --> 00:39:27,066
I got you the leverage
you needed to crack Ronnie.

1030
00:39:27,134 --> 00:39:29,502
You co-opted a sting
operation for your own gain.

1031
00:39:29,569 --> 00:39:31,937
And I solved another crime.

1032
00:39:32,005 --> 00:39:34,106
Identity theft. (chuckles)

1033
00:39:34,173 --> 00:39:37,109
Come on, admit it... we
solved this one together.

1034
00:39:37,176 --> 00:39:39,912
<i>Or are you too egotistical
to acknowledge my help?</i>

1035
00:39:41,681 --> 00:39:44,349
Okay, yeah, you didn't
completely destroy the case.

1036
00:39:44,417 --> 00:39:46,818
So you can stop blaming yourself, great.

1037
00:39:46,886 --> 00:39:48,319
Whatever do you mean?

1038
00:39:49,688 --> 00:39:52,289
The whole reason you tried
to prove Ty's innocence?

1039
00:39:52,357 --> 00:39:54,492
Was to catch the true culprit.

1040
00:39:56,261 --> 00:39:57,962
Yeah, sure.

1041
00:40:01,833 --> 00:40:04,167
LUCIFER: So I decided
not to punish myself.

1042
00:40:04,235 --> 00:40:05,903
Yourself?

1043
00:40:05,970 --> 00:40:08,138
Well, my fake self.

1044
00:40:08,205 --> 00:40:09,439
The person I'd kidnapped.

1045
00:40:09,507 --> 00:40:11,708
I decided not to beat him up.

1046
00:40:11,776 --> 00:40:14,210
(sighs) You were right, I was, um...

1047
